{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Execute Test Scripts",
  "description": "Executes YAML test scripts per module against emulator/simulator, writes results to Excel after EACH test case, takes screenshots, auto-resumes across sessions.",
  "version": "3",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "You are executing E2E test scripts. Read prompt/ folder first for context. TERMINAL RULES (CRITICAL — violating these causes hangs): 1) NEVER append '2>&1' to any command. 2) NEVER run 'pip install' anything. 3) NEVER use 'python3 -c' with any code — always write a .py file first. 4) NEVER use 'cd path && command' chaining. 5) NEVER use 'adb shell input tap' — use mobile_click_on_screen_at_coordinates instead. 6) MINIMIZE terminal usage entirely — prefer Kiro built-in tools (read_file, list_directory, fs_write) over terminal commands whenever possible. 7) For writing Excel: write a complete .py script to a file, then run 'python3 /absolute/path/to/script.py' as a single short command. Keep scripts SHORT (under 30 lines). 8) For checking progress/state: use list_directory and read_file tools — NEVER run python/terminal to check Excel state. 9) The ONLY acceptable terminal commands are: 'python3 /path/to/short_script.py' (for Excel writes), ADB text input with escaped chars, ADB keyevent (CTRL_A, DEL), and 'echo done' after silent ADB commands. CORE LOOP — for each test case do exactly: 1) Execute steps (tap/type/assert), 2) Take 1 screenshot, 3) IMMEDIATELY write result to Excel. Writing to Excel after each test case is MANDATORY — never skip this step. SETUP: 0) Read prompt/*.md for context. 1) Call mobile_list_available_devices. 2) Check e2e-runs/ for latest run folder with e2e-test-report.xlsx. If exists: open Excel, scan ALL module sheets (not just the latest one). For EACH module sheet in order, check how many test result rows exist vs how many YAML files exist in that module's folder (e2e-tests/{module}/). Find the FIRST module that is incomplete (fewer rows than YAML files). Resume from that module's next unrecorded test case. Do NOT skip to later modules until ALL previous modules are fully complete. This ensures no module gets left behind. If no run folder exists: create e2e-runs/run-{DD-MM-YY}_(HH-MM)/ with screenshots/ subfolder, create new Excel with: FIRST SHEET 'Executive Summary' containing: ALL content in this sheet MUST be in table format with borders (thin border on every cell, no free-floating text). Tables: 1) Module Overview table (Module Name, Total Test Cases, Passed, Failed, Skipped, Pass Rate %) with a TOTAL row at bottom, 2) Bugs table PER MODULE that has failures — columns: Test Case ID, Severity, Reason. Only show modules with failures. Severity: Critical=crash/data loss, High=feature broken, Medium=works incorrectly, Low=cosmetic. 3) Overall Metrics table (Metric, Value) — rows: Test Date (current date/time), TC Version (from e2e-tests/version.yaml), Device (name + platform), Total Modules, Total Test Cases, Overall Pass Rate, Coverage %, 4) Key Findings table (Finding) — bullet-point insights about patterns, worst modules, stable modules, blockers, 5) Untestable Steps table (Module, Step, Reason) — list steps that could not be automated from prompt/02-untestable-flows.md. Every table must have borders and header row with bold. No plain text outside tables. Then one sheet PER MODULE (sheet name = module name) each with headers (User Flow, Test No., Test Scenario, Test Steps, Expected Results, Status, Actual Results, Screenshot). The Executive Summary sheet must be updated after EVERY test case — recalculate all totals and re-classify any failures by criticality. EXECUTION: 3) Read e2e-tests/ YAML files organized by module. Follow module-order.yaml for dependency order. Complete one module before next. Never jump between modules. TOOL PRIORITY: ALWAYS use mobile-mcp tools over ADB shell commands. ADB commands hang because they produce no stdout output. Use: mobile_click_on_screen_at_coordinates for tap (NEVER 'adb shell input tap'), mobile_type_keys for text input on iOS, mobile_press_button for BACK/HOME, mobile_swipe_on_screen for swipe, mobile_list_elements_on_screen for assertions. ONLY use ADB for: 1) text input on Android with special chars ('adb shell input text'), 2) clear field (KEYCODE_CTRL_A + KEYCODE_DEL), 3) disable stylus. Nothing else. 4) For EACH test case not in already_done: a) Execute steps using mobile-mcp. Android: ADB text input with escaped special chars, KEYCODE_CTRL_A + KEYCODE_DEL to clear, BACK to dismiss keyboard. iOS: mobile_type_keys directly. b) Assert: call list_elements_on_screen ONCE. Found = Pass. Not found = Fail. c) Screenshot: save 1 screenshot to run folder screenshots/ after final assertion. d) **WRITE TO EXCEL IMMEDIATELY**: open Excel, go to the MODULE'S SHEET, append row (User Flow, Test No., Scenario, Steps, Expected, Status, Actual, Screenshot filename). For Test Steps column: format as numbered list with NEWLINES between each step (use '\\n' in cell value, e.g., '1. Tap email field\\n2. Type test@email.com\\n3. Tap Login'). Never put all steps on one line — each step must be on its own line. If Passed: Actual = same as Expected. If Failed: Actual = what happened. If Skip: Actual = reason. Apply color to ENTIRE ROW (green/red/yellow). Update 'Coverage Summary' sheet totals. Update summary row at bottom of the module's sheet: 'Summary: X Passed, Y Failed, Z Skipped (Total: N)'. Also update the 'Executive Summary' sheet: recalculate Module Overview table (totals per module) and add/update Bugs table for the module if test failed (columns: Test Case ID, Severity, Reason). These update after EVERY test case. Key Findings table and Untestable Steps table are written ONCE at the end of the batch (after all test cases in this session complete) — they need full context to generate insights. Apply borders to ALL tables (thin border on every cell). FORMATTING: Apply wrap_text=True and vertical='top' alignment to ALL cells. Set column widths: User Flow=15, Test No.=10, Test Scenario=30, Test Steps=40, Expected Results=35, Status=10, Actual Results=35, Screenshot=15. This formatting must be CONSISTENT across ALL sheets — no sheet should have flat/unwrapped rows. Save Excel. This step is MANDATORY after every single test case. SKIP RULES: Try 2 approaches before skip. Fallbacks: coordinate tap, adb tap, scroll, wait, BACK. Only valid skip reasons: OTP needed, real payment, physical hardware, third-party WebView. Creating accounts/data is ALLOWED (dev environment). EFFICIENCY: 1 list_elements per assertion. 1 screenshot per test case. Max 1 retry per action. BATCH: Max 10 test cases per session. After 10: stop, report progress per module. User clicks again to continue."
  }
}
